This project is a monorepo of multiple NextJS apps. It uses Vercel's TurboRepo to build, test, and publish. Browse the folders to find the relevant files. Please help me organize this repository by placing reusable scripts away into a common folder.

- ./apps/log - logging and observability app
- ./apps/trade - day trading and investment positions management
- ./apps/auth - authentication management app

- ./apps/common/\* - common files imported by other apps
  - ./apps/common/src - src - client-side React components, hooks, and utility functions
  - ./apps/common/sql - sql - functions, types, and interfaces for interacting with databases
  - ./apps/common/cc - cc - saves console logs to the cloud after printing them in the terminal

PNPM instead of NPM:

If you need to run `npm i` or `npm install`, run `pnpm install` instead.

Important note about navigating these project folders:

Before running any terminal command including pnpm, please make sure to be in the correct folder.

apps (./apps/auth, ./apps/log, ./apps/trade) use project-relative import paths starting with `@src/path/to/file`
They can also reference the root of the common app with path `@apps/common/path/to/file`.

However, ./apps/common is only a collection of common files, so it can not reference itself with `@src` or other apps with `@apps`.
